FL-26-Jul-2016

project: LINKS/CBG_PL_Conversion

The Python script CBG_PL_Convert.py converts an input .txt file to an output .csv file. 

In order to avoid encoding problems with the input file, the script tries to detect the 
used encoding of the input file with the Python "chardet" module. 

In general we use a previously created "virtualenv" python that contains all the needed 
extra modules for a given project. 

Use a previously created virtualenv python, e.g., on the Node-158 server:
	$ source /data/links/python352/bin/activate <ENTER>
	
Run the conversion script; at "input filename: ", type the name of the input file:
	$ cd /data/links/CBG_PL_Conversion <ENTER>
	$ python CBG_PL_Convert.py <ENTER>
	CBG_PL_Conversion
	input filename: Resultaat 1e vier letters.txt
	detecting input encoding...
	encoding: ISO-8859-2, confidence: 0.849336048104954
	output filename: Resultaat 1e vier letters.csv
	959 lines processed
	
[eof]
